02/04/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Parliament begins debate Wednesday (2 April) on constitutional changes as part of judicial reform.
The ruling National Movement Simeon II said Tuesday that parties in parliament have agreed on the proposed amendments.
The constitutional changes would affect magistrates' immunity and mandates.
(Trud, Standart, 24 Chassa, Sega - 02/04/03, BTA - 01/04/03)
